  <p>
    Everyone knows the sound: a toilet or drain that bubbles and gurgles after you run water
    somewhere else in the house. It's easy to ignore, but on a septic system it's worth a moment's
    attention, because a gurgle is literally the sound of air going where water should be flowing
    smoothly — and sometimes that's a small quirk, and sometimes it's an early warning.
  </p>

  {/* Intended asset: /images/resources/what-causes-drains-to-gurgle-hero.webp — see public/images/resources/README.md */}
